text:
Hi - just curious if anyone knows how to get all the even rows in a repeater? what I want to do is give all the even rows a specific class. I tried using loop.index but from what I've found, it only targets specific rows. Am I missing something? below is a sample of what I have and it works, but only for the second row. I tried loop.index == 'even' but that didn't work
```    {% for item in module.timeline_item %}
      &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
        &lt;div class="timeline-content {% if loop.index == '2' %}js--fadeInRight{% else %}js--fadeInLeft{% endif %}"&gt;
          &lt;h5&gt;{% inline_text field="timeline_title" value="{{ item.timeline_title }}" %}&lt;/h5&gt;
          {% inline_rich_text field="timeline_content" value="{{ item.timeline_content }}" %}
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    {% endfor %}```
